00:59:19.820 --> 00:59:20.620
I am a Viking.

00:59:20.820 --> 00:59:24.620
And a Viking that will not only help you unleash the Furies, but unleash yourself.

00:59:24.820 --> 00:59:26.620
It's in my Thor's Norse power program.

00:59:26.820 --> 00:59:27.620
Okay.

00:59:27.820 --> 00:59:29.620
I'm a little confused.

00:59:29.820 --> 00:59:31.620
Well, I'm a lot confused.

00:59:31.620 --> 00:59:35.420
I was taught in school that Vikings were bloodthirsty and violent.

00:59:35.620 --> 00:59:36.420
An elder once told me,

00:59:36.620 --> 00:59:38.420
You must unlearn what you have learned.

00:59:38.620 --> 00:59:40.420
Of course, then he died of the Green Plague.

00:59:40.620 --> 00:59:43.420
There are some Vikings that are a bloodthirsty lot, yes,

00:59:43.620 --> 00:59:45.420
but no more than anyone else, really.

00:59:45.620 --> 00:59:47.420
We're a nomadic people, Amy.

00:59:47.620 --> 00:59:49.420
We have cold fire in our souls.

00:59:49.620 --> 00:59:51.420
Ye have that fire, too, Amy.

00:59:51.620 --> 00:59:53.420
You've just lost it since you've gotten television.

00:59:53.620 --> 00:59:55.420
Now, that being said, I'll answer your question.

00:59:55.620 --> 00:59:57.420
We are mostly non-violent,

00:59:57.620 --> 00:59:59.420
though many of the Vikings travel to Scotland.

00:59:59.620 --> 01:00:00.420
And mind you,

01:00:00.420 --> 01:00:03.220
