01:00:11.420 --> 01:00:14.220
That's why, in my cassette series, I talk about the importance of communication.

01:00:14.420 --> 01:00:17.220
You see, Amy, men and women live in different worlds.

01:00:17.420 --> 01:00:19.220
We use different words.

01:00:19.420 --> 01:00:21.220
A group of men talk about what they've killed,

01:00:21.420 --> 01:00:24.220
how to start a fire, who has the best longboat.

01:00:24.420 --> 01:00:26.220
Women want to talk about keeping the community long,

01:00:26.420 --> 01:00:28.220
hot, tidy, and their feelings.

01:00:28.420 --> 01:00:29.220
When I'm raiding a village,

01:00:29.220 --> 01:00:31.020
I don't need to be talking about feelings.

01:00:31.220 --> 01:00:32.020
It's time for action.

01:00:32.220 --> 01:00:33.020
Great.

01:00:33.220 --> 01:00:35.020
So is that all there is to being a Viking?

01:00:35.220 --> 01:00:36.020
Pillaging?

01:00:36.220 --> 01:00:37.020
No, lass, no.

01:00:37.220 --> 01:00:39.020
Pillaging and battle are important.

01:00:39.220 --> 01:00:41.020
But we admire poetry as well.

01:00:41.220 --> 01:00:43.020
As long as it's poems about whacking someone

01:00:43.220 --> 01:00:45.020
