01:00:45.220 --> 01:00:47.020
What's holding you back, Amy?

01:00:47.220 --> 01:00:48.020
In chapter three of my book,

01:00:48.220 --> 01:00:50.020
I talk about listening to the bloodthirsty water spirit.

01:00:50.220 --> 01:00:53.020
It's really quite important if you want to enter Valhalla.

01:00:53.220 --> 01:00:55.020
I think I went there last night.

01:00:55.220 --> 01:00:57.020
Oh, no, that was Malibu.

01:00:57.220 --> 01:00:58.020
But it's the same sort of thing.

01:00:58.020 --> 01:00:59.820
Valhalla was that golf club, wasn't it?

01:01:00.020 --> 01:01:01.820
So 1983.

01:01:02.020 --> 01:01:02.820
But right.

01:01:03.020 --> 01:01:05.820
What does being a Viking have to do with anything?

01:01:06.020 --> 01:01:07.820
This is the 20th century.

01:01:08.020 --> 01:01:10.820
We have electricity, penicillin, jet planes, implants.

01:01:11.020 --> 01:01:12.820
Well, I don't, but I want some.

01:01:13.020 --> 01:01:14.820
But I heard the operation is really gross.

01:01:15.020 --> 01:01:17.820
You live like it's 982 A.D. or something.

01:01:18.020 --> 01:01:20.820
Mind ye tongue, wench, lest I cut it out.

01:01:21.020 --> 01:01:22.820
Deep down, all of you listening to me say,

01:01:23.020 --> 01:01:25.820
Thor, yes, I'd like to unleash the Viking within.

01:01:26.020 --> 01:01:27.820
Maybe you'll go camping once a year

01:01:27.820 --> 01:01:29.620
while hunting and wonder why it feels so natural.

01:01:29.820 --> 01:01:31.620
That's because it is.

01:01:31.820 --> 01:01:33.620
Too much of this denying your instincts.

01:01:33.820 --> 01:01:34.620
Men shaving.

01:01:34.820 --> 01:01:36.620
You know, deep down in the pit of your soul,

01:01:36.820 --> 01:01:38.620
you wish you could crouch in the grass

01:01:38.820 --> 01:01:40.620
with flies biting your face,

01:01:40.820 --> 01:01:42.620
afraid to move for fear of alerting the beasts,

01:01:42.820 --> 01:01:44.620
covering yourself with yak urine to thwart your smell.

01:01:44.820 --> 01:01:46.620
Then a beast draws close.

01:01:46.820 --> 01:01:49.620
You pounce, bringing your battleaxe on its skull.

01:01:49.820 --> 01:01:51.620
Man and animal at that moment,

01:01:51.820 --> 01:01:53.620
one and the same in a terrible beauty.

01:01:53.820 --> 01:01:55.620
Then you drag the carcass back to camp

01:01:55.820 --> 01:01:57.620
and celebrate by eating its heart.

01:01:57.620 --> 01:01:59.420
People, they only do this once in a lifetime.

01:01:59.620 --> 01:02:01.420
I do this every day, and so can you.

01:02:01.620 --> 01:02:03.420
All it takes is some positive thinking.

01:02:03.620 --> 01:02:06.420
Just attend my Unleash the Norse Within weekend.

01:02:06.620 --> 01:02:08.420
When you are finished, you will say,

01:02:08.620 --> 01:02:10.420
I am a god. Nobody can stop me.

01:02:10.620 --> 01:02:13.420
I crush my enemies and dance on their funeral pyres.

01:02:13.620 --> 01:02:16.420
This is very helpful for living in suburbia, Amy,

01:02:16.620 --> 01:02:17.420
and I should know.

01:02:17.620 --> 01:02:19.420
I really don't understand how.

01:02:19.620 --> 01:02:21.420
Oh, it's very helpful.

